            <title>[AMQ-6495] Boolean state flags in Failover transport should be volatile</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-6495</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Failover transport reconnect task looks at the started / disposed / shuttingDown flags to check if it should terminate but that value is read outside any locks and is not volatile leading to missing the not-started state.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
